History: -year-old female with altered mental status and history of seizures. Evaluate for aspiration or pneumonia.
Findings: Single frontal view of the chest. Lung volumes are very low and marked elevation of the left greater than right hemidiaphragm is similar to prior. Bibasilar atelectasis is unchanged. Cardiomediastinal contours are stable. Pulmonary vascular markings appear normal. No focal consolidation or large pleural effusion.
Impression: Low lung volumes without radiographic evidence of aspiration or focal consolidation.
